<br>
In fact, a level 50+ character will _never_ be hit for more than 2 by a level 1 mob that has a normal max hit of 4. But you don't see that reduction in max hit in any other circumstance, including the same character tanking a level 4 mob.<br>
<br>
It would, however, explain the reduction of effectiveness seen in some AC parsings. For some relative AC values, an increase will cause both some normal hits to become min hits and some max hits to become normal hits. For others, only one end of the range moves, making AC only half as effective.<br>
